cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses improvements to the SVRG algorithm for non-strongly convex or sum-of-non-convex objectives, which are commonly encountered in machine learning applications such as Lasso, logistic regression, stochastic PCA, and deep neural nets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
